n	&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;\n		.show-admin-bar {\n			display: none;\n		}\n	&lt;/style&gt;\n<span>&lt;?php</span>	\n<span>&#125;</span>\n&nbsp;\n<span>function</span> yoast_disable_admin_bar<span>&#40;</span><span>&#41;</span> <span>&#123;</span>\n   <span>if</span> <span>&#40;</span> <span>2</span> <span>==</span> get_current_user_id<span>&#40;</span><span>&#41;</span> <span>&#41;</span> <span>&#123;</span>\n      add_filter<span>&#40;</span> <span>\'show_admin_bar\'</span><span>,</span> <span>\'__return_false\'</span> <span>&#41;</span><span>;</span>\n      add_action<span>&#40;</span> <span>\'admin_head\'</span><span>,</span> <span>\'yoast_hide_admin_bar_settings\'</span> <span>&#41;</span><span>;</span>\n   <span>&#125;</span>\n<span>&#125;</span>\nadd_action<span>&#40;</span> <span>\'init\'</span><span>,</span> <span>\'yoast_disable_admin_bar\'</span> <span>,</span> <span>9</span> <span>&#41;</span><span>;</span></pre></div></div>\n\n<p>Or you could do the reverse, and enable the WordPress Admin Bar just for one user, by disabling it for everyone else:</p>\n\n<div><div><pre><span>&lt;?php</span> <span>function</span> yoast_hide_admin_bar_settings<span>&#40;</span><span>&#41;</span> <span>&#123;</span>\n<span>?&gt;</span>\n	&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;\n		.show-admin-bar {\n			display: none;\n		}\n	&lt;/style&gt;\n<span>&lt;?php</span>	\n<span>&#125;</span>\n&nbsp;\n<span>function</span> yoast_disable_admin_bar<span>&#40;</span><span>&#41;</span> <span>&#123;</span>\n   <span>if</span> <span>&#40;</span> <span>2</span> <span>!=</span> get_current_user_id<span>&#40;</span><span>&#41;</span> <span>&#41;</span> <span>&#123;</span>\n      add_filter<span>&#40;</span> <span>\'show_admin_bar\'</span><span>,</span> <span>\'__return_false\'</span> <span>&#41;</span><span>;</span>\n      add_action<span>&#40;</span> <span>\'admin_head\'</span><span>,</span> <span>\'yoast_hide_admin_bar_settings\'</span> <span>&#41;</span><span>;</span>\n   <span>&