/waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Nakaochiai-Gallery-and-Surrounding-Neighborhood.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(256,1,'2010-12-03 19:37:40','2010-12-03 19:37:40','','Screen shot 2010-07-23 at 11.33.17 PM','','inherit','closed','closed','','screen-shot-2010-07-23-at-11-33-17-pm','','','2010-12-03 19:37:40','2010-12-03 19:37:40','',0,'http://waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Screen-shot-2010-07-23-at-11.33.17-PM.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(593,1,'2010-12-05 21:18:34','2010-12-05 21:18:34','<a href=\"http://simplebits.com/\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-361\" title=\"SimpleBits\" src=\"http://waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Screen-shot-2010-12-05-at-5.40.42-PM-500x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"300\" /></a>','Simple Bits','','inherit','closed','closed','','360-revision-3','','','2010-12-05 21:18:34','2010-12-05 21:18:34','',360,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/12/05/360-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(268,1,'2010-12-21 12:45:05','2010-12-21 16:15:05','I\'m still not convinced that this is how you want to be doing this, but nevertheless the following will exclude posts of category 11 from showing up on the frontpage:\n\n[php]\nfunction exclude_category($query) {\n	if ($query-&gt;is_home){\n		$query-&gt;set(\'cat\',\'-11\');\n		}\n	return $query;\n	}\n\nadd_filter (\'pre_get_posts\', \'exclude_category\');\n[/php]\n\nPaste the code into your theme\'s <code>functions.php</code>.','Remove posts of a certain category from the frontpage','','inherit','closed','closed','','243-autosave','','','2010-12-21 12:45:05','2010-12-21 16:15:05','',243,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/12/03/243-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1212,1,'2011-01-24 19:48:39','2011-01-24 23:18:39','Morning light.','Morning Light','','inherit','closed','closed','','1210-revision','','','2011-01-24 19:48:39','2011-01-24 23:18:39','',1210,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2011/01/24/1210-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1213,1,'2011-01-24 19:49:45','2011-01-24 23:19:45','A square of morning light.<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1211\" title=\"IMG_3159\" src=\"http://waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/IMG_3159-500x375.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" />','Morning Light','','inherit','closed','closed','','1210-revision-2','','','2011-01-24 19:49:45','2011-01-24 23:19:45','',1210,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2011/01/24/1210-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1164,1,'2011-01-15 20:00:05','2011-01-15 23:30:05','Custom Posts introduced in Wordpress 3.0 give you the ability to create more than just blog posts. You can now create separate post types for all your content—photos, recipes, labels from your uncles 8-Track collection—you know, anything you can think of. This involves just two steps: Making a new post type and displaying the new posts.\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>First we need to tell WordPress about your new post type. Paste this into your <code>functions.php</code> file. If the file already has some code in there, omit the opening and closing PHP tags, if it doesn\'t leave them in. If your theme doesn\'t yet have a <code>functions.php</code> file, go ahead and make one. <code>Functions.php</code> should only have one set of opening and closing PHP tags.</li>\r\n	 [php] \r\n		&lt;?php\r\n			add_theme_support( \'menus\' );\r\n			add_action( \'init\', \'create_my_post_types\' );\r\n			function create_my_post_types() {\r\n				register_post_type( \'recipes\',\r\n					array(\r\n						\'labels\' =&gt; array(\r\n							\'name\' =&gt; __( \'Recipes\' ),\r\n							\'singular_name\' =&gt; __( \'Recipe\' )\r\n						),\r\n						\'public\' =&gt; true,\r\n					)\r\n				);\r\n			}\r\n		?&gt;	 \r\n	[/php] \r\n	 \r\n	\r\n	<li> Second (and last, whoot!) we want to display our new recipes for all the world to see, cook and enjoy. Paste this code anywhere you want to display your favourite recipes (may I recommend <code>sidebar.php</code>):</li>\r\n	\r\n	[php]\r\n	&lt;?php $loop = new WP_Query( array( \'post_type\' =&gt; \'recipes\', \'posts_per_page\' =&gt; 10 ) ); ?&gt;\r\n	&lt;?php while ( $loop-&gt;have_posts() ) : $loop-&gt;the_post(); ?&gt;\r\n\r\n	&lt;?php the_title( \'&lt;h2 class=&quot;entry-title&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;\' . get_permalink() . \'&quot; title=&quot;\' . the_title_attribute( \'echo=0\' ) . \'&quot; rel=&quot;bookmark&quot;&gt;\', \'&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\' ); ?&gt;\r\n\r\n	&lt;div class=&quot;entry-content&quot;&gt;\r\n		&lt;?php the_content(); ?&gt;\r\n	&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;?php endwhile; ?&gt;\r\n	 \r\n[/php]\r\n\r\nHat-tip to <a href=\"http://justintadlock.com/archives/2010/04/29/custom-post-types-in-wordpress\">Justin Tadlock</a> for this and many more great WordPress tricks.\r\n \r\n ','Creating and Displaying custom post types','','publish','closed','closed','','creating-and-displaying-custom-post-types','','','2011-01-15 20:13:21','2011-01-15 23:43:21','',0,'http://waterstreetgm.org/?p=1164',0,'post','',0),(305,1,'2010-10-15 19:45:51','2010-10-15 19:45:51','<p>After some recent criticism that brought to light the fact that this site was becoming &#039;somewhat&#039; Mac-centric, I decided to be more vigilant about spreading hatred and vitriol in the Windows direction. However, after helping a co-worker with a presentation on a Windows laptop today, I&#039;ve decided that only <em>more</em> hatred and vitriol are required, certainly not less.</p>\n\n<p>In several years of using a Mac I have not seen a single screen look like the one attached. But yet, this was the first screen I saw this morning when I started the laptop. I must argue that (i) it makes absoltuely no sense to show this screen to my Grandmother, my Great Aunts, nor to <em>anyone</em> else, and (ii) there is no way a screen like this one would show up on a Mac.</p>\n\n<p>Despite the abounding negativity from the naysayers about Apple these days, there&#039;s simply no way that a screen like this would be displayed to the user, and certainly you&#039;ll admit that it shouldn&#039;t. No?</p>\n<div class=\"field field-type-filefield field-field-photos\">\n    <div class=\"field-items\">\n            <div class=\"field-item odd\">\n                    <img  class=\"imagefield imagefield-field_photos\" width=\"640\" height=\"315\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://waterstreetgm.org/sites/default/files/sshot20091217020232.png?1287171948\" />        </div>\n        </div>\n</div>','On Macs and PCs, again','','inherit','closed','closed','','294-revision','','','2010-10-15 19:45:51','2010-10-15 19:45:51','',294,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/10/15/294-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2010-12-03 19:18:03','2010-12-03 19:18:03','I\'m still not convinced that this is how you want to be doing this, but nevertheless the following will exclude posts of category 11 from showing up on the frontpage:\r\n<pre>function exclude_category($query) {</pre>\r\n<pre>if ($query-&gt;is_home){</pre>\r\n<pre>$query-&gt;set(\'cat\',\'-11\');</pre>\r\n<pre>}</pre>\r\n<pre>return $query;</pre>\r\n<pre>}</pre>\r\n<pre>add_filter (\'pre_get_posts\', \'exclude_category\');</pre>','Remove posts of a certain category from the frontpage','','inherit','closed','closed','','243-revision-2','','','2010-12-03 19:18:03','2010-12-03 19:18:03','',243,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/12/03/243-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(358,1,'2010-12-05 17:08:57','2010-12-05 17:08:57','I\'m still not convinced that this is how you want to be doing this, but nevertheless the following will exclude posts of category 11 from showing up on the frontpage:\r\n[php]\r\nfunction exclude_category($query) {\r\n	if ($query-&gt;is_home){\r\n		$query-&gt;set(\'cat\',\'-11\');\r\n	}\r\n	return $query;\r\n}\r\n\r\nadd_filter (\'pre_get_posts\', \'exclude_category\');\r\n[/php]','Remove posts of a certain category from the frontpage','','inherit','closed','closed','','243-revision-5','','','2010-12-05 17:08:57','2010-12-05 17:08:57','',243,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/12/05/243-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(270,1,'2010-12-03 20:08:32','2010-12-03 20:08:32','<div id=\"_mcePaste\">\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\">\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><a rel=\"attachment wp-att-320\" href=\"http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/12/03/demolition/album-ryan-adams-demolition-2/\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-320 alignleft\" title=\"album-Ryan-Adams-Demolition\" src=\"http://waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/album-Ryan-Adams-Demolition1-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>If I had just three words, they’d all be: DEMOLITION. It’s most certainly an avenue you need need need to go down. But march forward not in haste! This is not an album you put on while having a glass of wine, warming up the barbeque and waiting for the onions to go translucent in the frying pan on Saturday evening.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">If you could choose, and surely you can, the time to listen to this album for the first (good) time, to get it at its absolute best, is to wait until you’ve lost faith in almost everything. At the very least wait until you reach a point when you’re looking for clarity of some kind, for although you won’t find any here, it should be a moving experience while you look.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">At its peak, this album is a big dash of cream in a large black, bitter coffee of a day. A strangely uncomfortable, deflating-then-uplifting smack in the gob of a cd that will leave you worse than you felt when you started, and surely leave you wondering why on earth you ever put it on in the first pace. But my God, do put it on.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The whole thing drips of October and Halloween, and of cool Fall air, and of lunchtime Anthropology seminars and the weekend when the clocks going back.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Demolition','','publish','closed','closed','','demolition','','','2011-01-11 09:43:14','2011-01-11 13:13:14','',0,'http://waterstreetgm.org/?p=270',0,'post','',0),(271,1,'2010-12-03 20:07:55','2010-12-03 20:07:55','<!-- p.p1 {m