u’re looking for clarity of some kind, for although you won’t find any here, it should be a moving experience while you look.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">At its peak, this album is a big dash of cream in a large black, bitter coffee of a day. A strangely uncomfortable, deflating-then-uplifting smack in the gob of a cd that will leave you worse than you felt when you started, and surely leave you wondering why on earth you ever put it on in the first pace. But my God, do put it on.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The whole thing drips of October and Halloween and cool Fall air and lunchtime Anthropology seminars and the clocks going back.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Demolition','','inherit','closed','closed','','270-revision-9','','','2010-12-04 00:37:41','2010-12-04 00:37:41','',270,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/12/04/270-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(316,1,'2010-12-04 14:34:46','2010-12-04 14:34:46','','10363-easy-tiger','','inherit','closed','closed','','10363-easy-tiger','','','2010-12-04 14:34:46','2010-12-04 14:34:46','',279,'http://waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/10363-easy-tiger.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(317,1,'2010-12-03 20:25:19','2010-12-03 20:25:19','<!-- p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px \'Lucida Grande\'} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px \'Lucida Grande\'; min-height: 15.0px} --> <!-- p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 26.0px \'Trebuchet MS\'; color: #ffffff; min-height: 30.0px} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 26.0px \'Trebuchet MS\'; color: #ffffff} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px \'Trebuchet MS\'; color: #ffffff} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 13.0px \'Trebuchet MS\'; color: #ffffff} p.p5 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px \'Lucida Grande\'; min-height: 13.0px} p.p6 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px \'Lucida Grande\'} p.p7 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 13.0px 0.0px; font: 13.0px \'Trebuchet MS\'} -->Having somehow missed this album entirely, I’m left constantly wondering—where has <em>Easy Tiger</em> been? I really have no explanation of how it slipped right through my hands all this time. Better still I suppose—where have I been?\r\n\r\n<em>Easy Tiger</em> demonstrates perfectly that Ryan Adams is so good because he writes really good songs that combine to form really good albums. No more or less than that. Good songs, and subsequent good albums. Somehow he manages to scratch down a dozen or so 3-4 minute songs that blend and fold together to make something else entirely. Together they form sadness, hope, enthusiasm, pain, longing, peril, and contentment - with all of the former endangering and supporting the achievement of the latter. He seems to be stretching upwards for some he can’t reach, or perhaps even see.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the cd he evokes an unbearably powerful feeling that I’m running away from and towards at the same time. And at an alarming pace. I find myself in one of these really frenetic, uncomfortable, wide-eyed places where the distance between from and towards is exactly the same. Somewhat like the proverbially uneasy, head-lighted deer.\r\n\r\n<em>Easy Tiger </em>was a truly incredible find, coming from a positively unbelievable oversight.','Easy Tiger','','inherit','closed','closed','','279-revision-4','','','2010-12-03 20:25:19','2010-12-03 20:25:19','',279,'http://waterstreetgm.org/2010/12/03/279-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2010-12-04 14:35:56','2010-12-04 14:35:56','','10363-easy-tiger','','inherit','closed','closed','','10363-easy-tiger-2','','','2010-12-04 14:35:56','2010-12-04 14:35:56','',270,'http://waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/10363-easy-tiger1.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(320,1,'2010-12-04 14:36:13','2010-12-04 14:36:13','','album-Ryan-Adams-Demolition','','inherit','closed','closed','','album-ryan-adams-demolition-2','','','2010-12-04 14:36:13','2010-12-04 14:36:13','',270,'http://waterstreetgm.org/wp-content/uplo